 from the seventh to the eighteenth centuries, presents the historical process of conversion to Islam in all its variety and unruly detail, through the eyes of both Muslim and non-Muslim observers.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aConversionxIslamvEarly works to 1800. 0aConversionxIslamxHistoryvSources. 7aRELIGION / Islam / History.2bisacsh1 aAbbou Hershkovits, Keren, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAnthony, Sean W., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAquil, Raziuddin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAzad, Arezou, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBauden, Frédéric, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBaxter Wolf, Kenneth, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBen-Dor Benite, Zvi, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBosanquet, Antonia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBrack, Jonathan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCarlson, Thomas A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aConterno, Maria, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCook, David, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCooperson, Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDeWeese, Devin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEphrat, Daphna, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFierro, Maribel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFrenkel, Yehoshua, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFriedmann, Yohanan, econtr